It quite frankly annoys me that people expect to have a job. That somehow they are entitled too a job. <br>
The other thing that annoys me is all this bullshit socialist government legislation, about how you can't just fire employees. Although I'm an employee, I would find it acceptable to be fired for being late, for taking lunch early, to not be 100% committed, or even that he/she didn't like me. Fact is... I feel I'm the best possible employee that my employer can get/afford, and if he wants to sack me, for whatever reason, then thats fine and his problem.<br>
<br>
Staff standing around? Sack them tomorow. Give them bad references(or at least brutally honest ones). If you can't get better new ones, then you should raise the pay. *shrug* Or re-employ them for £1.50/hour...<br>
<br>
You can employ me, but if its in retail, the minimum I want paid is £6/hour. Or £5/hour cash... I dont need holiday pay, paid sick leave or any of the other ridiculous things that are compulsary these days. :P<br>
<br>
<br>
Dash<br>
